   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER SEVEN GIVE UP THE WORLD CHRIST TO OBTAIN Scripture Reading: Heb 11:24-27; Phil 3:7-9a; 1 Cor 9:17; Eph 3:2; Col 1:25; Eph 2:20-22; 1 Cor 3:10; 2 Tim 4:7-8, 18a; 2 Cor 12:15a; Luke 16:9; 1 Thes 2:19-20; Matt 25:21, 23; Eph 4:11-16; 1 Tim 3:15-16 OUTLINE Examples in the Bible: The footsteps of Moses Heb 11:24-27: By faith refusing to be called the son of Pharaoh's daughter v. 24.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Choosing rather to be ill-treated with the people of God than to have the temporary enjoyment of sin v. 25.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Esteeming the reproach of the Christ greater riches than the treasures of Egypt v. 26a.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Looking away to the reward v. 26b.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>By faith leaving Egypt v. 27a.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>As seeing the invisible One v. 27b.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The image of Paul Phil 3:7-9a: Counting what things that were gains to him as loss on account of Christ v. 7.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Counting all things to be loss v. 8a.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>On account of the excellency of the knowledge of Christ v. 8b.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Suffering the loss of all things and counting them refuse that he may gain Christ v. 8c.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Being found in Christ v. 9a.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Rewards from gaining Christ: Moses: Becoming the one to usher in the Old Testament ministry: Establishing the law a testimony of God among men Exo 25:16.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Building the tabernacle a habitation of God among His people Exo 25:8-9.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Being qualified to enter the kingdom Matt 16:28 17:3; Heb 11:26b.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Paul: Becoming the one to usher in the New Testament ministry 1 Cor 9:17; Eph 3:2.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Completing the word of God the revelation of God's New Testament economy Col 1:25.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Building up the Body of Christ the habitation of God in the universe Eph 2:20-22; 1 Cor 3:10.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Receiving the kingdom 2 Tim 4:7-8, 18a.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The coming joy that results from being spent for Christ 2 Cor 12:15a: Being welcomed into the eternal tabernacles by those who receive benefit from you Luke 16:9.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>Having the ones that have received your help as your crown and joy at the coming of Christ 1 Thes 2:19-20.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Participating in the joy of Christ in the kingdom Matt 25:21, 23.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Completing the New Testament ministry Eph 4:11-12: Building the church of God 1 Tim 3:15-16.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>As the pillar and base of the truth v. 15.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>As God's manifestation in the flesh v. 16.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>For the building up of the Body of Christ Eph 4:12-16.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Arriving at the oneness in practicality v 13a.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Arriving at a full-grown man v. 13b.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>Arriving at the measure of the stature of the fullness of Christ v. 13c.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>No longer babes v. 14.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>Holding to truth in love, growing up into Him in all things, who is the Head, Christ v. 15.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>Out from the Head all the Body, fitted and knit together through every joint of the supply, according to the operation in measure of each one part, causing the growth of the Body unto the building up of itself in love v. 16.</S>
   </TEXT>
